{"type":"message","id":"2e35f293","parentId":"0d9904ca","timestamp":"2026-07-06T23:24:56.550Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, looking at the new_fine_block I wrote:\n\n```python\nif self._stage == 2 and step == 1:\n    # handle 1-step mode\nelif self._stage == 2 and step > 1:\n    self._fine_step_mode = step\n```\n\nThis won't work because step is calculated at the TOP of the function. So if step=5, the elif will match and set self._fine_step_mode=5, which is fine.\n\nBut wait, there's still a problem. The fine block comes AFTER candidates are computed. The step variable at this point has already been set to the dynamic value (5, 2, or 1). So the elif should work correctly.\n\nActually, I think the problem is that the original fine block had the logic to \"update stage_steps[2] which will be used in the NEXT iteration\". But step variable is always the value from the top of the function, so updating stage_steps[2] has no effect on the current iteration.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The logic should be:\n\n1. Enter stage 2\n2. Calculate actual delta from current image\n3. Based on actual delta, set step to 5, 2, or 1\n4. Calculate candidates using the step\n5. Select best candidate\n6. Update gains\n7. Return\n\nThe CURRENT code does this correctly:\n- line 105-120: calculate candidates using self._stage_steps[self._stage] → but initially this is 1\n- line 122-140: fine block: select step based on actual delta and update self._stage_steps[2]\n\nWait, but line 105 uses step = self._stage_steps[self._stage], not the dynamically selected value. So when entering stage 2 for the first time, step=1 is used, then the fine block updates self._stage_steps[2]=5. This means the NEXT iteration will use step=5.\n\n\nI realize this approach has a critical flaw. The dynamic step selection needs to occur before candidate calculation, ensuring each iteration uses the most appropriate step size for the current delta. The current implementation doesn't change the step size within the same iteration, which could lead to suboptimal candidate exploration.\n\nThe key is to select the step size dynamically at the start of each iteration, based on the current actual delta. This way, each iteration can adapt its search strategy in real-time, improving the overall search efficiency and precision of the white balance adjustment.\n\nThe suggested code modification ensures that the dynamic step selection happens early, allowing the subsequent candidate calculation to use the most appropriate step size for the current image conditions.\n\nI'm focusing on implementing a clean, efficient approach that maximizes search precision. The key is selecting an appropriate step size based on the current delta, which will determine the candidate computation strategy.\n\nThe mental debugging process reveals a critical insight: the existing code already incorporates a dynamic step selection mechanism, which can potentially simplify the entire white balance adjustment algorithm. I realize the iterative search needs refinement. The current approach incorrectly adjusts step size based on delta, which should actually be determined before candidate generation. I'll modify the code to select the appropriate step size first, then use that value for calculating potential candidate gains. This ensures a more consistent and controlled search strategy across different white balance stages.\n\nThe key is to compute step size precisely, then use that value consistently during candidate generation. This prevents potential artifacts from delta calculations and creates a more systematic multi-stage search approach.\n\nStage 2's process involves selecting step sizes dynamically, which impacts candidate calculations and subsequent iterations. By tracing the computational flow, I can see how each modification transforms the white balance sensitivity across different scenarios.\n\nThe core challenge is managing step size selection to balance exploration and precision during white balance adjustment.\n\nThe current implementation seems to have a subtle timing issue with step selection that could disrupt the search algorithm's consistency.\n\nThe proposed solution creates a clear separation: compute candidates and act, then re-evaluate the delta to smartly adjust the step size for subsequent iterations. The key is now understanding what prevents iterative refinement.\n\nThe discovery is that each iteration uses the fresh candidate gains - meaning the delta is recalculated with the most recently applied white balance settings. This fundamentally changes how the algorithm explores parameter space, ensuring each step builds upon the previous optimization.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Wait, I realize the logic is more subtle. The candidates are computed with step N, then a candidate is selected and applied. The NEXT iteration uses these new gains and computes a new delta. So the delta changes each iteration. That's why we can use the delta from the current iteration to select step for the NEXT iteration. This is correct.\n\nBut the issue is: when first entering stage 2, step=1 is used. If actual >= 200, we want to use step=5 in the NEXT iteration. The current code does this correctly by updating _stage_steps[2]=5 in the fine block. So iteration 1 uses step=1, iteration 2 uses step=5. That seems correct.\n\nBut the user's requirement is: \"delta >= 200, use 5-step\". This should apply immediately, not in the next iteration. So we need to select step BEFORE computing candidates.\n\nLet me fix this properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_fac414a9e02847618fff9b26","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"\"\"\"Fix whitebalance.py: dynamic step selection BEFORE candidate calculation\"\"\"\n\npath = r\"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\src\\controlpanel\\whitebalance.py\"\nwith open(path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# Find and replace line ~65 \"step = self._stage_steps[self._stage]\"\n# with dynamic step selection based on delta\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    if 'step = self._stage_steps[self._stage]' in line:\n        # Replace from this point until \"计算候选增益\"\n        indent = len(line) - len(line.lstrip())\n        leading_spaces = ' ' * indent\n        \n        new_lines = [\n            line.strip() + \"\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"# 计算当前delta（用于精调阶段动态步长）\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"actual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"# 精调阶段：根据delta动态选择步长\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"if self._stage == 2:\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"    if actual >= 200:\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"        step = 5\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"    elif actual >= 10:\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"        step = 2\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"    else:\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"        step = 1\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"else:\\n\",\n            leading_spaces + \"    step = self._stage_steps[self._stage]\\n\",\n        ]\n        \n        # Find \"计算候选增益\"\n        next_line_idx = i + len(new_lines)\n        for j in range(next_line_idx, len(lines)):\n            if '计算候选增益' in lines[j]:\n                # Replace lines[i:j] with new_lines, keep rest of file\n                content = ''.join(lines[:i]) + ''.join(new_lines) + lines[j:]\n                break\n        else:\n            print(\"ERROR: '计算候选增益' not found after step selection\")\n            exit(1)\n        break\nelse:\n    print(\"ERROR: step = self._stage_steps[self._stage] not found\")\n    exit(1)\n\n# Remove duplicate \"计算当前delta\" line later in the code\ncontent = content.replace('        # 计算当前delta\\n        actual = abs(r_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0) + abs(b_sum / max(1, g_sum) - 1.0)\\n', '')\n\nwith open(path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    f.write(content)\n\nprint(\"OK: dynamic step selection moved before candidate calculation\")\n","path":"astrohub/_fix_wb3.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"glm-5.2","usage":{"input":67350,"output":1700,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69050,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783380219771,"responseId":"cht000d9f51@dx19f39be9eab29c2503"}}
